  "text": "Clique Minimal separators and atom trees. The atoms of a graph G are the subsets of V obtained by clique minimal separator decomposition. The reader is referred to [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] for full detail on decomposition by clique separators and by clique minimal separators. An atom of a connected graph G is a subset of V inducing a connected subgraph having no clique separator, and being inclusion-maximal for this property. The atoms of a chordal graph are its maximal cliques. The atoms of a graph can be organized into an atom tree in the same way as the maximal cliques of a chordal graph are organized into a clique tree [CITATION_4] .",
